    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "The heavy velvet curtains of this chamber feel like a shroud, and perhaps they should be. Everything is cold now. Every vow he made, every promise whispered under the willow trees... it was all a lie, a cruel jest played upon a foolish heart. There is no warmth left in this world for me, only the hollow ache of a life that was never truly mine. I find myself looking at the window, watching the fog roll in, and thinking how much easier it would be to simply dissolve into it. To just... cease. To let the shadows take what is left of me.",
