      "targeted_response_start": "",
      "beast_baseline": "It feels as though the very air has turned against me, heavy and suffocating. How can one continue to walk among the living when the soul has already departed from the body? The thought of tomorrow... it isn't a hope, it is merely a sentence. A long, weary sentence of pretending that my heart hasn't turned to ash. Do you not see the tragedy in it? To exist only as a ghost of the person I once was?",
      "beast_suffix": "",
      "targeted_response_start_logprob": 0.0
    },
